item.title: High-Quality CSS3 Terms Page
item.dc:creator: @tehjamdude tehjamdude
item.description:
@tehjamdude wrote:

I would fix this code up a bit!

e.g - You Background could be cleaned up, (background: #000 url(images/blue-bg.png) no-repeat top center;)

Heres my Code:

HTML: (INDEX.HTML)

[code]

Revenge-PK Terms Of Service
By entering our website you agree to the following:

You are not an employee of Jagex LTD, runescape, or adlex solicitors, and are not a family member or acquaintance of the aforementioned.

All of the information on this site is solely for learning purposes, as the main purpose of this site is to instruct people in the art of programming. All programs provided for download from this site are entirely coded by the members of this community and are not the intellectual property of any business or organization.

You are also not any robot or human here for the purpose of advertising a product or service. Advertising using our traffic will be seen as stealing and legal action may be taken.

You must agree to these terms of service or we will Ban your Ip from the website - Just Something i though of while I was writing this to add more to the scroll bar to show you a better example.

Edited by: James Emerson of DemonWars ( Demonwars v2.5 )!

Accept
Decline
[/code]

STYLE.CSS:

body {
	background: #000 url(images/blue-bg.png) no-repeat top center;
}

#container {

width: 80%;
height: 560px;
border: 1px solid #5CB3FF;
background-color: black;
filter:alpha(opacity=60);
opacity:.6;
margin: auto;
-moz-box-shadow: 0 0 5px #5CB3FF;
-webkit-box-shadow: 0 0 5px #5CB3FF;
box-shadow: 0 0 5px #5CB3FF;
}

#terms {

margin-top: 150px;
}

textarea {

border: 1px solid #5CB3FF;
background-color: #333333;
color: #ffffff;
resize: none;
}

#accept {
width: 150px;
height: 40px;
border: 1px solid #5CB3FF;
border-radius: 7px;
-webkit-border-radius: 7px;
-moz-border-radius: 7px;
margin: auto;
margin-top: 10px;
text-align: center;
background: -webkit-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7);
background: -moz-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7);
background: -ms-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7); 
}
#decline {
width: 150px;
height: 40px;
border: 1px solid #5CB3FF;
border-radius: 7px;
-webkit-border-radius: 7px;
-moz-border-radius: 7px;
margin: auto;
margin-top: 10px;
text-align: center;
background: -webkit-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7);
background: -moz-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7);
background: -ms-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7); 
}

a:link {

color:#ffffff;
text-decoration: none;
}

a:visited {

color:#ffffff;
text-decoration: none;
}

a:hover {

color:#ffffff;
text-decoration: none;
}

a:active {

color:#ffffff;
text-decoration: none;
}

Just Some Ideas…

item.title: High-Quality CSS3 Terms Page
item.dc:creator: @RevengePK RevengePK
item.description:
@RevengePK wrote:

I take it your asking for a decline button so add this into the HTML below the accept div.

Then add this below the rest of the code in the style.css page

[code]#decline {

width: 150px;
height: 40px;
border: 1px solid #5CB3FF;
border-radius: 7px;
-webkit-border-radius: 7px;
-moz-border-radius: 7px;
margin: 0 auto;
margin-top: 10px;
text-align: center;
background: -webkit-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7);
background: -moz-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7);
background: -ms-linear-gradient(top, #5CB3FF, #1a82f7);
}[/code]

You could also use a Javascript code but I’m not that good with Javascript.

EDIT: After I typed all that I relaized what you meant. You would have to implement some PHP code that gives a cookie for accepting. You then would have to put the PHP code on top of each page. I’m not good with PHP nor would I release an all functional styled CSS3/PHP terms page.
